1
00:00:01,067 --> 00:00:02,633
You said that earring was yours
<i> but it wasn't.</i>

2
00:00:02,633 --> 00:00:04,133
<i>I didn't tell you
the truth  because</i>

3
00:00:04,133 --> 00:00:05,400
<i> I know this would happen.</i>

4
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:07,367
[JUSTIN] No matter how many
times  you file a report,

5
00:00:07,367 --> 00:00:08,767
<i> you won't know anything.</i>

6
00:00:08,767 --> 00:00:10,600
<i> Mom had nothing to do with it,</i>

7
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:11,867
<i> nor any of us for that matter.</i>

8
00:00:11,867 --> 00:00:13,767
[MARTIN]<i> Where's the signature
</i> of the tourism officer?

9
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:15,200
[SARI] He hasn't signed it yet.

10
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,500
<i> It's just one signature, Sari!</i>

11
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:19,300
<i>Look, just wait for three days
and Sari will resign then.</i>

12
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:20,700
<i> - Are you sure of that?
- Oh!</i>

13
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:23,533
[GIO]<i> I was in town earlier to
</i> talk  with a possible sponsr

14
00:00:23,533 --> 00:00:24,767
<i> for the music festival.</i>

15
00:00:24,767 --> 00:00:26,667
<i>They said they wanted to
talk with the general manager.</i>

16
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:27,900
<i> That's you, isn't it?</i>

17
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:30,600
[JADE]<i> We're talking about
</i> my mother, okay?

18
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,767
[KIKO] But it's my father
being investigated  here.

19
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,267
<i> So, just make me a promise.</i>

20
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:36,300
[EDWARD] Oh, they're here, Jade.
Let's go?

21
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:38,133
<i> I thought we had a meeting.</i>

22
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:40,367
<i>Why? Are we not allowed
to have a meeting on a boat?</i>

23
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:43,667
[JADE INHALES DEEPLY]

24
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:53,767
["PANGHABANG IKAW" BY
DARREN ESPANTO PLAYS]

25
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:56,567
[EDWARD] I already talked with
a group of influencers.

26
00:00:56,767 --> 00:00:59,367
They will arrive at the hotel
ahead of the music fest.

27
00:00:59,367 --> 00:01:00,500
So, Jade...

28
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,767
let's make sure that they'll
have a good experience

29
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:05,333
at the hotel and
on the island, okay?

30
00:01:05,767 --> 00:01:07,367
Really?

31
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,800
Is that why we'll be
island-hopping?

32
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:14,633
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

33
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:16,167
Of course.

34
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:19,767
I also want to know how
island-hopping is with you.

35
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,400
Should it really just be me?

36
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:24,733
Why? Who's the Head
of Marketing here?

37
00:01:25,767 --> 00:01:28,333
- Isn't it you?
- Yeah.

38
00:01:28,533 --> 00:01:31,100
Don't tell me that you think...

39
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:33,600
I just want to be alone
with you?

40
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:34,767
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

41
00:01:34,767 --> 00:01:35,933
[EDWARD SCOFFS]

42
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:38,367
Do you think I just
want to be with you?

43
00:01:38,367 --> 00:01:39,667
Hell no!

44
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:41,733
How delusional!
I never said anything like that.

45
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:43,767
You're the delusional one.

46
00:01:44,567 --> 00:01:46,700
That's what you were
talking about, right?

47
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:48,300
[SCOFFS] Of course, not.

48
00:01:48,867 --> 00:01:50,433
Of course.

49
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:52,400
Yes.

50
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:58,800
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

51
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:01,367
Hey! Hey, hey, hey!

52
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:03,600
What are you doing?

53
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:14,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

54
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:36,767
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

55
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:58,767
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

56
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,133
[JADE] Hey!

57
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,167
Edward!

58
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:17,133
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

59
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:35,333
[PLAYFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:36,467
Edward!

61
00:03:37,733 --> 00:03:40,333
Hey! Edward! Edward!

62
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,467
Edward!

63
00:03:41,667 --> 00:03:42,767
Hey!

64
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,633
What are you doing?

65
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:49,467
We have a meeting, don't we?

66
00:03:49,467 --> 00:03:54,400
- [WATER SPLASHING]
- [PLAYFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

67
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:55,733
We're in the sea!

68
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:57,000
There are no rules here!

69
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,800
Dive in, let's have
a meeting here instead.

70
00:04:00,267 --> 00:04:01,433
I don't want to.

71
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:03,233
I'm not in the mood, okay?

72
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:05,267
Okay, fine.

73
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:07,333
But just like I said earlier,

74
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:10,500
I promised the influencers that
they'll get to dive

75
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,500
and island-hop too.

76
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:14,500
The hotel can do that, right?

77
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:16,500
But just so you know,

78
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:19,967
the influencers I contacted have
at least 500k followers, okay?

79
00:04:19,967 --> 00:04:21,967
I can imagine it already.

80
00:04:21,967 --> 00:04:23,400
Once they post...

81
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,467
Boom!

82
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:26,967
People will automatically
book a room in Hotel 88.

83
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,433
Isn't that right?

84
00:04:28,433 --> 00:04:31,267
[PLAYFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

85
00:04:31,267 --> 00:04:34,300
Jade! Were you listening to me?

86
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,967
[STUTTERS] Oh, yes. Yes.

87
00:04:42,667 --> 00:04:43,833
[JADE]<i> We'll still proceed
</i> as planned.

88
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:45,633
<i> Wait for me when we get back.</i>

89
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:50,533
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

90
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:53,767
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

91
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:55,967
You don't have to open
the door for me.

92
00:04:55,967 --> 00:04:57,267
It's fine, sir. Don't mind me.

93
00:04:57,267 --> 00:04:58,800
- Gandara!
- Hey!

94
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,967
How are you doing?
You have a cool ride, huh?

95
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,667
It's just work.

96
00:05:02,667 --> 00:05:04,600
- Gandara! Gandara!
- Send my regards to Julie!

97
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,667
Oh, hello!

98
00:05:05,667 --> 00:05:06,667
How are you and
your grandfather?

99
00:05:06,667 --> 00:05:08,433
We're doing fine.
Grandpa still looks great.

100
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:10,667
Of course! Who else are
you going to take after?

101
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:12,500
- Oh, that's a lot.
- Take some home.

102
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,900
- Oh, no, it's fine!
- Just take some.

103
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,833
- It's for you and your grandpa.
- Okay then.

104
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:18,500
Hey, how have you been?
Thank you so much!

105
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:19,733
Are you running for
a position here?

106
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:23,333
[SARI GIGGLES]
Sir, you're so funny!

107
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:24,800
I'm not kidding.

108
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,833
Well, sir, I'm a little...

109
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:28,433
Just a little, okay?

110
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:31,067
I'm a little bit popular
in our town.

111
00:05:31,067 --> 00:05:33,733
I always win pageants here.

112
00:05:33,733 --> 00:05:36,033
That's why they call me "Ganda."

113
00:05:36,467 --> 00:05:39,933
[SARI] And, sir,
I'm not trying to brag but

114
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:42,067
I've never lost
a single pageant.

115
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:43,167
So, you know, sir, sometimes--

116
00:05:43,167 --> 00:05:45,933
You're quite talkative,
aren't you?

117
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:47,000
[SARI CHUCKLES]

118
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,433
You're so-- [EXCLAIMS]

119
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:49,633
Sorry, sir.

120
00:05:49,633 --> 00:05:52,000
- You're so funny, sir.
- Is the tourism officer inside?

121
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,000
- [STUTTERS] Uh, yes!
- We might wait too long.

122
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,833
I've spoken to his secretary.

123
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,633
I said we were already here.

124
00:05:58,667 --> 00:05:59,667
Um...

125
00:05:59,667 --> 00:06:01,667
Why did you choose
to have a music festival?

126
00:06:01,667 --> 00:06:02,800
[LUNA CHUCKLES]

127
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,667
It's simple, ma'am.

128
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:06,433
A lot of money will come in

129
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:08,567
both for us and for you.

130
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:12,567
And your product, Planet Mobile,
will be promoted too.

131
00:06:12,933 --> 00:06:16,600
Um, haven't a lot of people
done that already?

132
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:19,367
It's starting to feel like...

133
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:21,000
it's repetitive.

134
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,367
What's unique about this one?

135
00:06:23,367 --> 00:06:26,833
And, uh, what does it mean
to you, personally?

136
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,400
Um...

137
00:06:28,933 --> 00:06:30,933
Well, for me,

138
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:34,500
music is the only place where
people stop pretending.

139
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,900
[LUNA] There are
no titles nor status.

140
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:41,033
Whoever you are, you're all
equal at the music festival.

141
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:43,767
This is the kind of crowd

142
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:46,467
you'll want your brand
to be associated with.

143
00:06:46,467 --> 00:06:49,433
Real people, real connections.

144
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,167
Hmm...

145
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:53,000
I don't know.

146
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,000
Also--

147
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,167
Ma'am.

148
00:06:55,167 --> 00:06:59,167
Let me just add that
this music fest we're proposing

149
00:06:59,167 --> 00:07:02,167
this not just about
music or headliners.

150
00:07:02,167 --> 00:07:04,167
Personally, it's more
about memory.

151
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:07,567
So, this is the kind of night
that people will remember.

152
00:07:08,067 --> 00:07:10,400
You may not know this but...

153
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:13,000
Luna was a DJ back then.

154
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:13,933
Oh, really?

155
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:16,067
She has always had
a unique energy that

156
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:18,700
can connect to people
through music.

157
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:21,467
And that's what we want to
happen with our music festival.

158
00:07:21,467 --> 00:07:23,767
To connect with people,
whether or not they're locals.

159
00:07:23,767 --> 00:07:24,767
Hm.

160
00:07:24,767 --> 00:07:28,467
I like the way you see things,
Mr. Cabrera.

161
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:29,467
Just call me Gio.

162
00:07:29,467 --> 00:07:31,100
[SPONSOR] Oh, sure. Gio.

163
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:32,700
Oh, by the way,
do you have a card?

164
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,467
Of course, I have.

165
00:07:34,467 --> 00:07:37,833
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:39,000
[GIO] Here.

167
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,400
[SPONSOR] Okay.

168
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:41,867
Okay then.

169
00:07:41,867 --> 00:07:44,100
I'll just get in touch
with you, okay?

170
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:45,200
[GIO] Okay, ma'am.

171
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:47,067
I still have a meeting
to attend to,

172
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:49,400
so I'll leave
the two of you alone.

173
00:07:50,633 --> 00:07:51,800
Thank you, ma'am.

174
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,567
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

175
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:55,200
I'll just give you a call then.

176
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,500
Thank you.

177
00:07:59,533 --> 00:08:00,767
[LUNA EXHALES SHARPLY]

178
00:08:03,867 --> 00:08:06,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

179
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:09,533
Wait a minute.
Why do you seem angry?

180
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:11,100
I got the sponsor
to say yes, didn't I?

181
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,933
Yeah. Thanks to you.

182
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:14,600
Are you angry because
you got overshadowed?

183
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,733
No.

184
00:08:16,167 --> 00:08:18,000
What's wrong with what I did?

185
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,867
[LUNA] Nothing.

186
00:08:18,867 --> 00:08:20,233
Nothing? Then why
do you seem angry?

187
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:22,600
I just don't like it when others
speak on my behalf, Gio.

188
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:23,767
About what?

189
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:27,867
Who are you to tell others
that I was a DJ?

190
00:08:27,867 --> 00:08:29,233
Well, isn't it true?

191
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:30,967
Why don't you want her to know?

192
00:08:30,967 --> 00:08:32,567
You know nothing!

193
00:08:32,567 --> 00:08:36,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:37,233
Luna!

195
00:08:39,933 --> 00:08:41,067
Luna!

196
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:50,200
[WAVES LAPPING]

197
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,500
[GROANS SLIGHTLY]

198
00:08:52,867 --> 00:08:53,833
[JADE SQUEALS]

199
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,200
Seriously?!

200
00:08:55,733 --> 00:08:57,333
Are you doing that
on purpose, huh?

201
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,533
Jade, when the influencers
arrive,

202
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:02,500
you can't be
acting like that, okay?

203
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:04,500
Why? What's wrong with me?

204
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,400
That! Exactly that.

205
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,333
You don't seem to know
how to have fun.

206
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:09,433
[JADE SNICKERS]

207
00:09:09,433 --> 00:09:11,433
You probably don't even know
how to make a joke.

208
00:09:11,433 --> 00:09:14,967
Oh yeah? Since when was
making jokes a requirement?

209
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,900
What about you?
Do you even know how to joke?

210
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:18,867
Ah...

211
00:09:19,567 --> 00:09:20,867
Are you challenging me?

212
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:23,500
Fine.

213
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,700
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

214
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:28,867
Which fish is important?

215
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:30,300
I don't know.

216
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:32,567
You're not even going
to think about it?

217
00:09:32,567 --> 00:09:34,700
Okay, fine!
You're the expert at jokes.

218
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:35,867
I just don't feel like thinking.

219
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:36,800
Then it's...

220
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,867
"Es-fish-cial."

221
00:09:42,433 --> 00:09:43,700
Fish!

222
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:45,367
- "Fish-cial" "Es-fish-cial."
- That's so corny. So corny.

223
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:47,400
Cut it out, that's corny.
So corny.

224
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:49,900
Corny? You want another one?

225
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:50,900
No.

226
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,967
So grumpy!

227
00:09:58,067 --> 00:10:05,000
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:10:16,867 --> 00:10:17,867
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

229
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:26,500
Did anyone use this truck
after the owner died?

230
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,733
No, sir.

231
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:30,800
Even Sir Mike's children
never touched it.

232
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:35,433
Okay. Thank you.

233
00:10:37,033 --> 00:10:43,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

234
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:46,700
If there really was a folder,
where could it have gone?

235
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:49,100
We were at the
actual crime scene.

236
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:50,333
There was no folder.

237
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,833
Do you think
what I said helped?

238
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:59,900
It looks like it made them think
when you mentioned the folder.

239
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:01,767
That was new information
for them too.

240
00:11:02,667 --> 00:11:04,867
It's a shame I really forgot
about it back then.

241
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,633
That folder just slipped
my mind.

242
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:08,667
Same here.

243
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,867
A lot of things were
happening at the time.

244
00:11:10,867 --> 00:11:12,400
[PHONE CHIMES]

245
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:20,167
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

246
00:11:20,167 --> 00:11:21,367
Who's that?

247
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,133
Uh, no one.

248
00:11:23,733 --> 00:11:25,533
Who's that?
You're smiling. Let me see.

249
00:11:25,533 --> 00:11:27,167
- It's nothing!
- Who is it?

250
00:11:27,167 --> 00:11:29,500
- Monette, it's nothing.
- Who is it?

251
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,900
[MONETTE]<i> Congratulations,
</i> Raphael Salcedo!

252
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:32,900
<i> We are excited to inform you</i>

253
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,700
<i>that you have been
officially accepted</i>

254
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:38,833
<i>to the
University of the Arts Manila.</i>

255
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:41,967
<i>Your creative journey
starts here.</i>

256
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,033
You applied?

257
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,200
Huh? Uh--
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

258
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,300
Well...

259
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:48,200
I just tried.
It's nothing serious.

260
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:50,833
And I don't even really
want to go there, okay?

261
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:54,500
I'll just stay here.
Always right beside you.

262
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:57,633
Besides, it's just the
two of us in this world.

263
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:59,100
Why would I choose
to move away, right?

264
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:01,700
Are you sure?

265
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,633
Uh. Monette, come on.

266
00:12:03,633 --> 00:12:05,200
I told you, it was nothing.

267
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:07,733
You know, I just made
a bet with...

268
00:12:07,733 --> 00:12:08,900
With Rona.

269
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:10,700
I told her I'd get accepted.

270
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:11,967
And I did.

271
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:13,667
But it's nothing.

272
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:15,700
Look, I'll delete it now.

273
00:12:16,167 --> 00:12:18,500
Hmm. It's deleted.

274
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:21,833
- Raphie, if you want to--
- I don't.

275
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:25,067
Monette, let's not talk
about this anymore.

276
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:29,033
Oh, there you are.

277
00:12:29,033 --> 00:12:30,167
Sir Justin!

278
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:31,633
Sir Justin, you were just there.

279
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:33,100
We've been looking for you.

280
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:34,867
Why?

281
00:12:34,867 --> 00:12:37,467
Oh, we have a guest
who wants to go island hopping.

282
00:12:37,467 --> 00:12:38,933
But aren't you from recreation?

283
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:40,533
[GAME SOUNDS FROM PHONE]

284
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:41,633
Damn!

285
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:44,133
Who even is that guest?
What a nuisance!

286
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:47,567
What?!

287
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:50,633
Why didn't you say
you weren't coming to work?

288
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:52,700
[SIGHS]

289
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:55,633
Fine. [SIGHS]

290
00:12:55,633 --> 00:12:56,667
Fine, fine.

291
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,767
There's nothing I can do
about that.

292
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:01,733
- What did he say?
- So annoying.

293
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:04,033
We don't have a boatman!

294
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:06,733
He said he's sick,
so he can't come in.

295
00:13:06,733 --> 00:13:07,833
I don't know about him!

296
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:10,600
Just cancel that island hopping.

297
00:13:11,067 --> 00:13:13,000
That's a waste.

298
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,167
[RAPHIE] This way, ma'am.

299
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:16,933
Ma'am is here!

300
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:18,567
She's already excited.

301
00:13:19,133 --> 00:13:26,067
- [GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WIND CHIME RINGS]

302
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,300
[MONETTE] Oh my, ma'am.

303
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:33,567
The boatman isn't here.
They said it's canceled for now.

304
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:34,500
Oh, no, no, no.

305
00:13:35,033 --> 00:13:36,033
It's fine now.

306
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,067
[MONETTE STAMMERS]
Huh? I thought--

307
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,767
It's fine, alright?

308
00:13:39,767 --> 00:13:40,967
[MONETTE] Okay.

309
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:45,967
I'll take care of it.

310
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,667
Alright, I'll go get changed.

311
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,700
Okay.

312
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:59,100
[DOOR OPENS]

313
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,267
[SIGHS]

314
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:03,700
[DOOR CLOSES]

315
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:05,133
We didn't find anything
the first time.

316
00:14:06,233 --> 00:14:07,833
But whatever was
inside that folder,

317
00:14:07,833 --> 00:14:10,267
I'm sure it was important.

318
00:14:11,133 --> 00:14:12,100
[SIGHS]

319
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,967
No matter how important
that folder is,

320
00:14:13,967 --> 00:14:15,767
if we can't find it,
it doesn't matter.

321
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:18,233
It's not even in
Michael Fernandez's truck.

322
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,533
[EXHALES]

323
00:14:21,667 --> 00:14:23,200
What if it got lost
at the crime scene?

324
00:14:24,567 --> 00:14:25,633
So?

325
00:14:25,633 --> 00:14:30,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

326
00:14:30,367 --> 00:14:31,767
That means...

327
00:14:33,167 --> 00:14:35,133
It's possible someone else
was there.

328
00:14:38,167 --> 00:14:39,233
[EXHALES]

329
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:41,367
Who could that be?

330
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:48,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

331
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:02,033
- [WAVES CRASHING]
- [BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

332
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:06,300
Will we wait for a boat,
or will we ride this?

333
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:07,900
Nope.

334
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:08,900
No?

335
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:10,400
How are we going to leave?

336
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:12,733
This is the tour.

337
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:14,900
Welcome to Isla...

338
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:15,967
Solara!

339
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:19,067
It's beautiful, isn't it?

340
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:20,767
I booked for
an island-hopping experience.

341
00:15:20,767 --> 00:15:22,767
That's what I paid for.
This is not it, okay?

342
00:15:22,767 --> 00:15:23,933
- I want a refund.
- Hey!

343
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:25,133
This is more fun
than island hopping.

344
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:26,500
And look at the waves,
it's strong today.

345
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:27,567
That's why it's safer here.

346
00:15:27,567 --> 00:15:30,333
And it's safe here,
as long as...

347
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:31,967
I am with you.

348
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,467
[WOMAN] Justin...

349
00:15:38,467 --> 00:15:40,267
- [SLAPS]
- [GRUNTS]

350
00:15:40,267 --> 00:15:41,867
[WOMAN] How dare you?

351
00:15:41,867 --> 00:15:43,300
Are you dating Angel
and me at the same time?

352
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:45,900
Huh? Who's Angel?

353
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:48,100
Stop denying it.
You went out on Friday

354
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:49,967
after we went out on Thursday.

355
00:15:49,967 --> 00:15:52,167
And now you're with someone new?

356
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:53,967
Uh, excuse me.

357
00:15:53,967 --> 00:15:56,100
I'm a guest at Hotel 88.

358
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:59,433
I'm not one of his girls
for your information.

359
00:15:59,433 --> 00:16:01,467
Are you sure?

360
00:16:01,467 --> 00:16:03,833
My god, you're such a player!

361
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:05,100
Look.

362
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:06,233
I went out with you on
a Thursday

363
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:07,833
and went out on
a Friday with Angel.

364
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:08,833
If I wanted to date you both,

365
00:16:08,867 --> 00:16:10,033
I would've asked you
both out on Thursday.

366
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:12,933
Besides, we're not
really exclusive, right?

367
00:16:12,933 --> 00:16:14,267
You're so shameless!

368
00:16:14,267 --> 00:16:15,967
Don't come near me again!

369
00:16:17,133 --> 00:16:18,300
Step aside.

370
00:16:19,533 --> 00:16:20,833
Woah!

371
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:26,067
Do you have a boyfriend?

372
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:30,900
- You are unbelievable!
- Oh!

373
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,433
Don't mind that girl.

374
00:16:32,433 --> 00:16:34,500
Should we hang out after this?

375
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,933
[SARI] You told me earlier
she was there.

376
00:16:36,933 --> 00:16:38,567
I still messaged you earlier,
remember?

377
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,533
[RECEPTIONIST] She left again.

378
00:16:40,533 --> 00:16:43,100
[SIGHS] We've been here
for quite some time,

379
00:16:43,133 --> 00:16:45,500
can we ask for
a follow-up, please?

380
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:47,967
- [SIGHS]
- [KEYBOARD CLACKING]

381
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:50,000
Do you see my handsome boss?

382
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,367
He's good-looking,
but he has a short temper.

383
00:16:52,367 --> 00:16:55,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

384
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:57,267
- [KEYBOARD CLACKING]
- [SIGHS]

385
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:58,400
He's already mad!

386
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,233
Oh my god!
I'll just check on him.

387
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:01,500
Hold on.

388
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:03,833
Sir...

389
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:06,267
[MARTIN] We've
been waiting here for hours.

390
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:08,500
Do you know how important
every minute is to me?

391
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:12,533
[CLICKS TONGUE] Sir, they told
me that she's there.

392
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:15,967
She's here?

393
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,600
Where?

394
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:20,167
Tell me, Sari, where is she?

395
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:21,433
Where is she?

396
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:22,933
Am I blind?

397
00:17:22,933 --> 00:17:25,300
Are my glasses broken?

398
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:28,167
You told me she's here,
so where is she?

399
00:17:28,167 --> 00:17:31,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES, FADES]

400
00:17:31,867 --> 00:17:34,200
You're just wasting my time.

401
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,633
How incompetent.

402
00:17:35,633 --> 00:17:37,433
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

403
00:17:37,433 --> 00:17:38,600
Sir Martin!

404
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:44,533
Could I please get
an update? Please?

405
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:50,267
Where are you going?
Our tour isn't over!

406
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:54,333
[WAVES CRASHING]

407
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:57,200
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

408
00:17:57,200 --> 00:18:00,167
The foot traffic is strong...

409
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:03,133
and the demographics are right.

410
00:18:03,133 --> 00:18:05,100
It just needs the right owner.

411
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:12,133
- [WAVES CRASHING]
- [BRIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]

412
00:18:15,233 --> 00:18:17,167
I like your smile.

413
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:20,967
I knew you liked me too.

414
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:23,200
[SCOFFS] Whatever.

415
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:24,467
[CHUCKLES]

416
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:32,500
Raphie, find me a new assistant.

417
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:35,267
Someone quiet, skilled and
knows what they're doing.

418
00:18:35,267 --> 00:18:38,267
What's going on, sir?
What happened to Sari?

419
00:18:38,267 --> 00:18:41,367
Did she resign?
Did I win the bet?

420
00:18:41,367 --> 00:18:43,100
What are you talking about?

421
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:45,567
Just find me a new one, ASAP!

422
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:47,433
- Okay?
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

423
00:18:47,433 --> 00:18:49,233
Sir! Sir! Sir!
Wait! Wait! Wait!

424
00:18:49,233 --> 00:18:51,333
I'm going home.
Do whatever you want.

425
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:54,033
Sir, wait! The tourism officer
will talk to you now.

426
00:18:54,033 --> 00:18:56,033
She's already there. [PANTING]

427
00:18:56,067 --> 00:19:03,033
[CURIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

428
00:19:08,633 --> 00:19:11,767
It's chaotic. Noisy.

429
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:14,367
I'm sure only young people
will come here.

430
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:16,400
Alright, I still have somewhere
else to go.

431
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,600
[SIGHS] Ma'am.

432
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:20,267
For sure, most of them
will be young people.

433
00:19:20,733 --> 00:19:22,700
But I'm also sure
they won't be the only ones

434
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:24,633
who'll be interested
in our music festival.

435
00:19:24,633 --> 00:19:25,800
The last time something
like that happened

436
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:26,867
here on the island,

437
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:29,233
your father, Michael,
was the one leading it.

438
00:19:29,633 --> 00:19:30,933
[OLD TOURISM OFFICER]
You know what happened?

439
00:19:30,933 --> 00:19:33,000
Well, it even sparked trouble.

440
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:35,467
A lot of people fought.

441
00:19:35,467 --> 00:19:38,000
Because they were drunk.

442
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:40,933
Ma'am, that was a long time ago.

443
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:44,033
And strict security
is already part of our plan.

444
00:19:44,033 --> 00:19:45,700
[OLD TOURISM OFFICER]
Even so.

445
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:46,667
Change it.

446
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,367
Just hold a mass instead.

447
00:19:48,367 --> 00:19:49,867
More people would be happy.

448
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:51,267
But, ma'am--

449
00:19:52,333 --> 00:19:55,033
[OLD TOURISM OFFICER]
Your father just died,

450
00:19:55,033 --> 00:19:57,300
and you're already doing
all sorts of things.

451
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:59,300
Ma'am, it's 2026!

452
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:01,800
Yet you still think so backward.

453
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,433
No wonder this island
is being left behind.

454
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,300
You may leave now.

455
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:08,667
I still have things to do.

456
00:20:09,767 --> 00:20:10,733
Hilda...

457
00:20:10,733 --> 00:20:11,733
- Let's go.
- Sir!

458
00:20:11,733 --> 00:20:12,967
We won't get anything from here.

459
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:15,533
Sir, wait! Just stay put.
[SIGHS]

460
00:20:22,033 --> 00:20:23,833
Ma'am! One moment, please!

461
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:25,867
Just a second.
Wait a minute, please.

462
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:29,333
I just remembered
what my grandfather said.

463
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:32,033
Why would I care about
what your grandfather said?

464
00:20:32,033 --> 00:20:33,767
Uh! Ma'am! [PANTS]

465
00:20:33,767 --> 00:20:35,567
My grandfather said,

466
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:38,000
if you fight with someone
or hurt someone's feelings

467
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,433
during festival week,

468
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:41,900
you'll have bad luck on
this island for the whole year.

469
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:43,867
Would you want that?

470
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:49,367
I've heard that saying too.

471
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:52,433
Is your grandfather, Botong?

472
00:20:52,433 --> 00:20:55,433
Exactly! That's my grandfather!

473
00:20:55,433 --> 00:20:57,567
Did you know he was
the one who predicted

474
00:20:57,567 --> 00:21:00,033
that I would grow old here
at the municipal office,

475
00:21:00,033 --> 00:21:02,500
serving our people?

476
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:04,467
Oh, really? Oh my, ma'am!

477
00:21:04,467 --> 00:21:06,467
You're not the only one
my grandfather predicted

478
00:21:06,467 --> 00:21:08,633
whose fortune came true.
There are many of you.

479
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,967
Now I remember!

480
00:21:10,967 --> 00:21:13,067
- You were always with him!
- [SARI CHUCKLES]

481
00:21:13,067 --> 00:21:15,800
You were still
so tiny back then.

482
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,100
[SARI That's what
I remember too.

483
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:18,333
You're still the same.

484
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:20,567
Nothing has changed.
You're still beautiful.

485
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:21,667
[OLD TOURISM OFFICER
CHUCKLES]

486
00:21:21,667 --> 00:21:23,600
[SARI CHUCKLES]

487
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:25,767
Ma'am...

488
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:28,933
About our event at Hotel 88...

489
00:21:28,933 --> 00:21:30,833
I promise, cross my heart!

490
00:21:31,667 --> 00:21:34,600
[SARI] Our security
is really tight.

491
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,733
Sir Martin is from Manila.

492
00:21:36,733 --> 00:21:38,467
He knows a lot
about these things.

493
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:39,800
All that security stuff.

494
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:41,000
It's on another level.

495
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,900
- They are like terminators.
- [TOURISM OFFICER LAUGHS]

496
00:21:42,933 --> 00:21:44,767
Would you like that, ma'am?

497
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:47,100
So please, ma'am...

498
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:50,467
Go ahead and sign this permit.

499
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:53,833
[SIGHS] If it weren't
for your grandfather Botong.

500
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:59,067
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

501
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:00,533
[SARI] Thank you, ma'am.

502
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,467
[CHUCKLES]

503
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:03,667
Thank you, ma'am.

504
00:22:08,767 --> 00:22:15,700
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

505
00:22:18,467 --> 00:22:23,067
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

506
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:24,833
Don't follow me.

507
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:26,467
- Why would I even follow you?
- Let's split up first.

508
00:22:26,467 --> 00:22:27,800
[GIO SCOFFS]

509
00:22:29,467 --> 00:22:34,100
[BOAT ENGINE WHIRRING]

510
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:45,033
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

511
00:23:00,067 --> 00:23:07,033
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

512
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:29,067
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

513
00:23:29,767 --> 00:23:31,033
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

514
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:33,167
<i>I'm just here to collect
the remaining  debt you owe.</i>

515
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:34,767
<i>We are going to make
a dance trend.</i>

516
00:23:34,767 --> 00:23:37,233
<i>That way, they'll see us
having fun in Hotel 88.</i>

517
00:23:37,233 --> 00:23:38,833
<i> - Oh, Jade!
- Are you okay?</i>

518
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:41,067
<i> - Are you okay?
- I'm fine, I'm fine.</i>

519
00:23:41,067 --> 00:23:42,400
<i> Sir, I have good news for you.</i>

520
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:44,400
<i>You have a new candidate
to interview</i>

521
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:46,233
<i> for your future assistant!</i>

522
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:48,800
<i> I am Justin Almazan.</i>

523
00:23:49,233 --> 00:23:50,400
<i> At your service.</i>

524
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,067
<i> So, you're an Almazan?</i>

525
00:23:52,067 --> 00:23:54,833
<i>About the flowers,
who sent them?</i>

526
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:57,000
<i> Someone sent you flowers?</i>

527
00:23:57,033 --> 00:23:59,100
<i>It's just like what
your dad used to give me.</i>

528
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:02,267
Didn't the police return to you
<i> your father's phone?</i>

529
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:03,567
<i>We might be able
to find something there.</i>

530
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:05,533
I'll also check my dad's phone.

531
00:24:07,167 --> 00:24:09,167
<i>Are we still doing
